  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "Here are some troubleshooting steps to resolve Viber connection issues on PC:\n\n1. Check Internet Connection\n- Ensure your computer has a stable internet connection\n- Try visiting other websites to confirm connectivity\n\n2. Restart Viber\n- Close the Viber application completely\n- Reopen the application\n\n3. Check Viber Settings\n- Verify your login credentials\n- Ensure you're using the same Viber account on mobile and PC\n\n4. Update Viber\n- Download and install the latest version of Viber\n- Check for any available updates\n\n5. Check Firewall/Antivirus\n- Temporarily disable firewall/antivirus\n- Add Viber to allowed applications\n\n6. Clear Viber Cache\n- Go to Viber settings\n- Clear cache and data\n- Restart the application\n\n7. Reinstall Viber\n- Uninstall the current version\n- Download and install the latest version from the official website\n\n8. Check Network Configuration\n- Restart your router\n- Try using a different network connection\n\nIf none of these steps work, contact Viber support for further assistance.",
